The paper deals with communication channels and probability mass functions, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and its subfield of information theory and probability (cs.ITP). The algorithm proposed in the paper, Geometric Huffman Coding, involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also touches on the topic of signal processing (cs.SI) in the context of modulating signals for transmission over channels.
